@page "/donate"

<section class="donate-hero">
    <h1>Support Ripple</h1>
    <p>
        Your contribution helps us grow fresh, sustainable food for communities facing food insecurity 
        in the Chicagoland area. Every donation strengthens our mission and expands our impact.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="donate-section">
    <h2>Why Your Support Matters</h2>
    <p>
        Ripple operates a year‑round aquaponics facility that produces fresh leafy greens and tilapia 
        for local food pantries and community partners. Your donation helps us:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Increase food production for families in need</li>
        <li>Maintain and expand our aquaponics systems</li>
        <li>Support educational workshops and community programs</li>
        <li>Fund research that improves sustainability and efficiency</li>
        <li>Build a scalable model for other communities to replicate</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="donate-section">
    <h2>How to Donate</h2>
    <p>
        Ripple is in the process of registering as a <strong>501(c)(3)</strong> nonprofit organization 
        in Illinois. Once approved, all donations will be tax‑deductible. In the meantime, you can still 
        support our mission by contributing through our secure donation portal.
    </p>

    <div class="donate-box">
        <a href="#" class="btn donate-btn">Make a Donation</a>
        <p class="donate-note">
            (Donation link placeholder — replace with your payment processor when ready.)
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="donate-section">
    <h2>Other Ways to Support Ripple</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Volunteer at our facility</li>
        <li>Partner with us for community programs</li>
        <li>Share our mission with friends and family</li>
        <li>Attend workshops and educational events</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="donate-section">
    <h2>Thank You</h2>
    <p>
        Your generosity helps us grow food, grow community, and grow hope. Thank you for supporting 
        a more sustainable and equitable future for Chicago.
    </p>
</section>
